# Scripts and DB Access

## Decision Table

| Goal | Command | DB Target |
|------|---------|-----------|
| Start remote Dagster UI (tunnels + webserver) | `poetry run remote-ui` | Remote (tunnel) |
| Run Dagster locally with remote DB (fast debug) | `poetry run local-matchmaking` | Remote (tunnel) |
| Set up local Postgres + migrations | `poetry run setup-db` | Local |
| Deploy code to remote server | `poetry run deploy` | — |
| Launch matchmaking run (remote) | `./scripts/launch_remote_matchmaking_run.sh <partition>` | Remote |
| Launch skill verification (remote) | `./scripts/launch_candidate_skill_verification.sh [partition]` | Remote |
| Deploy + instructions | `./scripts/run_remote_matchmaking.sh [partition]` | — |
| Inspect matches/candidate/job on **local** DB | `poetry run with-local-db python scripts/inspect_*.py <partition>` | Local |
| Inspect matches/candidate/job on **remote** DB | `poetry run with-remote-db python scripts/inspect_*.py <partition>` | Remote |
| Run any DB script on local DB | `poetry run with-local-db python scripts/<script>.py ...` | Local |
| Run any DB script on remote DB | `poetry run with-remote-db python scripts/<script>.py ...` | Remote |

## Prerequisites for Remote DB

`poetry run remote-ui` **or** `poetry run local-matchmaking` must be running (SSH tunnel to remote Postgres). The tunnel maps remote Postgres to `localhost:POSTGRES_REMOTE_TUNNEL_PORT` (default 15432).

## Poetry Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `remote-ui` | Start Dagster UI locally; tunnels to remote Postgres + gRPC. Jobs run on remote. |
| `local-matchmaking` | Run Dagster dev locally; code executes on your machine, DB via tunnel to remote. |
| `setup-db` | Start local Postgres (Docker) and run migrations. |
| `deploy` | Git pull + docker compose rebuild on remote. |
| `with-local-db` | Run a command with `POSTGRES_HOST=localhost`, `POSTGRES_PORT=5432`. Loads `.env` automatically. |
| `with-remote-db` | Run a command with `POSTGRES_HOST=localhost`, `POSTGRES_PORT=15432` (or `POSTGRES_REMOTE_TUNNEL_PORT`). Loads `.env` automatically. |

## Shell Scripts (use directly)

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `./scripts/launch_remote_matchmaking_run.sh [partition]` | Launch ats_matchmaking_pipeline run. Requires remote-ui or local-matchmaking running. |
| `./scripts/launch_candidate_skill_verification.sh [partition]` | Launch skill verification for a candidate. Requires remote-ui running. |
| `./scripts/run_remote_matchmaking.sh [partition]` | Deploy to remote, then print instructions to launch run. |

## DB Target Summary

| Target | Host | Port | When |
|--------|------|------|------|
| **Local** | localhost | 5432 | Local Docker Postgres, setup-db |
| **Remote (tunnel)** | localhost | 15432 (or `POSTGRES_REMOTE_TUNNEL_PORT`) | remote-ui or local-matchmaking running |

## .env Configuration

- `POSTGRES_HOST`, `POSTGRES_PORT` — local DB (default 5432)
- `POSTGRES_REMOTE_TUNNEL_PORT` — local port for SSH tunnel to remote Postgres (default 15432)
- `REMOTE_HOST` — SSH target (e.g. `root@89.167.123.152`)

All configuration is in `.env`; no manual env export needed when using `with-local-db` or `with-remote-db`.
